review_blob: Bottle, pours almost black with very very very thick tan head, that is more annoying than anything, has an interesting smell more of a macro pilsner than anything, taste is sweet with definite chocolate and cinnamon and pumpkin tastes, do like the taste way better than expected. tastes like a pumpkin ale to me

Bottle. Pour a bold orange color with a thick white head. citrus notes in the aroma, taste is a very smooth bitter, nothing over the top. finishes a bit sour with the lasting hop flavor. Pretty good lil beer here
Draft at the brewery,pours golden orange with little head, smell is citrus-y and earthy. Taste is straigth hop bitterness and is really smooth. Just a step up from the IPA!

bottle, pours black, with little head. Smell is smokey with some chocolate and light alcohol scent. Taste is similar, more smoke than anything though, very well done seeing as how i found it at the grocery store after the beer stores had closed

bottle, pours light orange with a thick white head that has great lacing. has a hoppy earthy smell with a hint of citrus. Mouthfeel is good and taste is very generic hoppy IPA. If someone were to ask me what an IPA tastes like i think this is a very good generic deScription... Definitely enjoyable
bottle pours black, with thin tan head and no retention. mostly smoke aroma, a little spice as well as alcohol too. Taste is a straight campfire smoke. not bad, not amazing, worth a try i guess.

bottle, pour very dark orange with a thick off white head, no lacing. Definite chocolate aroma, some bourbon as well, kind of reminds me of a faint GI bourbon county stout. Taste is smokey and chocolatey with slight alcohol mouthfeel.  smooth palate for me, just like most browns. Very Very VERY average beer here.
beer_name: Left Hand Deep Cover Brown Ale

review_blob: Bottle. Pours a hazy gold, with medium white head and good lacing. The aroma is of citrus mostly, but you can definitely smell the hops. Taste is very light citrus, very more of the bitterness of the various hops. the light sweetness adds a good undertone. Very easy to drink and a very well done Golden, which is usually one of my least favorite styles

bottle. Pours a hazy orange with little to no head. Aroma is sweet and hoppy, smells like sugar. Tastes sweet, definite orange taste with a very smooth hoppy spice. This is a classic, dont give up on it based on the aroma beer. suprisingly tasty!

bottle.Pours dark dark brown, with little tan head. The aroma is straight coffee with a little liquer. Very Smoky taste, rich coffee and chocolate. Goes down smooth and is very enjoyable. could drink this every night!

Pours a golden orange with very little head and no retention. Aroma is spicy, definitely smell the cinnamon and the pumpkin, also can smell some vegetable undertones, for some reason zuchinni pops at me. Taste is spicy with the same cinnamon and pumpkin. I think since they call it a pumpkin Ale, they are hitting the nail on the head. Good for once, not sure id be looking forward to it all year.

Pours Light amber color, with a medium head. Aroma is a rotten sour smell that is faint and hard to identify. The taste is rather sweet, with a hint of bitterness. cannot tell this is a 10% beer. Pretty decent barleywine. Dont give up on it just based on the aroma, I would even recommend to taste before you smell.

Bottle Thanks to CaptainCougar. Pours light amber color with little off white head that did not retain long. The Aroma is very soft, not much there maybe a little citrus. Then you take a drink and your hit with a spicy and bitter palate that is very delicious. Hops definitely abundant, and in a very good way. Glad to have this one

12 oz bottle. pours orange with a medium white head. aroma is of citrus most notably grapefruit with hint of lemon. Taste is sweet citrus but can definately taste the hoppiness. I enjoy this one over and over
While this beer is exactly what it says it is, exactly what it says it it is just not very good. tastes like a chocolate cover cherry, thats it
bottle at old chicago, Poured light amber color with yellowish tan head. Spice aroma and taste, never would have guessed 7 abv. great aftertaste of bitter spice, nice beer here
bottle for old chicago, pretty good winter ale warm roasty and toasty taste and aroma. finishes smooth with some roasty aftertaste

Had this on tap in KC and did not care for it at all. aroma was earthy and slightly alcoholy to me. Taste was something i cant pinpoint but i didnt enjoy it, kind of bitter i guess. If this is their most popular beer i will not be going back for more!
Didnt see the high praise everyone else gets with this one. Poured real dark with a thin head.Taste was malty and toasty pretty in your face taste to me. may need to try this again

I didnt have much expectations for this one, but I actually kind of enjoyed it, a nice easy drinking roasty porter, for those looking for the porter aroma and taste and a beer you can drink a few of, this is a viable option
I really enjoyed this porter, poured dark brown with medium tan head. Rosted malt aroma that was pretty strong. Taste was the same, very full bodied and smooth.

Very Very Very average porter, nothing really stood out and made me want to go buy more. Poured a lighter shade of brown than most porters, not much head, Aroma was chocolately and almost a little oily to me. Taste was rather bland of chocolate and a hint of alcohol. just not my favorite beer

Pours Dark Brown with very thin tan head, aroma is smokey with hints of caramel and roasted almonds. Palate is very smooth and taste is smoky and toasty with slight sweet caramel hints. pretty good small town porter

Black Appearance with very little khaki head from the tap. Everything about this is chocolately the taste the smell, everything. I loved it very easy drinker for how dark it was. Also, definately reccommend this as a car bomb, way better than guiness, thanks the the barkeep!

Aroma is of coffee and vanilla with a hint of smoke, Taste has definite vanilla cream coffee taste, very smooth and doesnt feel too heavy, definitely something you can enjoy 4-5 of. Tallgrass definitely has a winner
Hazy orangeish gold color with a thick white head, aroma is of strong citrus, palate is smooth and leaves a citrus taste. More drinkable than previous ratings made me expect
Actually got the chance to drink this and then brew it, now i have enough for a long while! thick off white head, very chocolatey aroma, the malt is very smooth and a great easy drinker. tasty!
On Tap at Old Chicago, Very thin tan head, had very strong roasted aroma and taste very smooth and not much sting for  the ABV, pleasantly suprising from 23rd St.
